         <div type="translation" resp="part:kuch">
 	<p n="1-6"><gap reason="lost"/> offered servants, cows <gap reason="lost"/><supplied reason="subaudible">and</supplied> silver. The paddy field <supplied reason="subaudible">called</supplied> Tnal Teṁ Trāc <gap reason="lost"/> chanel; the paddy field <supplied reason="subaudible">called</supplied> Vrai Hvāṅ, the paddy field <gap reason="lost"/> which was cultivated <supplied reason="subaudible">by</supplied> Mratāñ Yajamāna <gap reason="lost"/> Tāṅ Yajamāna, the paddy field Ramayoṅ <gap reason="lost"/> <supplied reason="subaudible">paddy field called</supplied> Nojña which Vraḥ Añ Yajamāna offered to <gap reason="lost"/>.</p>
            <p n="7-10">All these paddy fields which have been offered to the god <gap reason="lost"/>. <supplied reason="subaudible">Those</supplied> who take away the treasure of the god will go to hells <supplied reason="subaudible">and</supplied> will suffer in the hells as long as the Sun and the Moon exist.</p>
         </div>
